Mirabito Energy Products CEO Joseph P. Mirabito Named 2015 STOP-DWI MADD Award Recipient

April 29, 2015Brent Strignano 




(Binghamton, NY) The Broome County STOP-DWI Program today announced that Mirabito Energy
Products CEO Joseph P. Mirabito has been awarded the 2015 NYS STOP-DWI Foundation and Mothers
Against Drunk Driving New York State (MADD) Non-Law Enforcement Award for his support of
young driver education held in conjunction with the Mirabito STOP-DWI Holiday Classic.
 
“Mr. Mirabito and Mirabito Energy Products have gone above and beyond in every way possible in their
support of young driver education provided by the Broome County STOP-DWI Program,” said Broome
County Executive Debbie Preston. “Without the support of Mr. Mirabito and the entire Mirabito Energy
Products team, the Broome County STOP-DWI Program would not be able to conduct the amount of
young driver education that it currently does on a yearly basis. The support given to this program has no
doubt had an immediate and long-lasting impact on the mindset of our young drivers and will save lives
for many years to come.”
 
By partnering with Mirabito Energy Products, the STOP-DWI Program has been able to expand its
young driver education program to include the following:
 

Conducting 79 impaired-driving presentations to 4,284 students in 20 schools districts around the Southern Tier over the past 3 years
Hosting a 5-hour traffic safety seminar for over 300 student athletes participating in the STOPDWI Holiday Classic basketball tournament on an annual basis
Co-hosting Teen Traffic Safety Day at which over 1,300 students from 16 school districts come together for a full day of interactive activities, guest speakers, and traffic safety competitions
Partnering with local school districts to provide a law enforcement presence at high-profile high school events to deter and detect alcohol use amongst students
Working with Mirabito convenience stores to reduce underage drinking

 
Since 1995, New York State highway safety partners have proudly hosted this annual recognition to
acknowledge outstanding efforts and achievements in deterring impaired driving. This recognition
program is supported by member agencies of the Governor’s Traffic Safety Committee, the NYS STOPDWI
Foundation and MADD.
For more information about Broome County STOP-DWI please visit: www.bcstopdwi.com  


 





